eral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) with panels extending to 228 antibodies to construct a multimodal reference atlas of the circulating immune system. Multimodal analysis substantially improves our ability to resolve cell states, allowing us to identify and validate previously unreported lymphoid subpopulations. Moreover, we demonstrate how to leverage this reference to rapidly map new datasets and to interpret immune responses to vaccination and coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19). Our approach represents a broadly applicable strategy to analyze single-cell multimodal datasets and to look beyond the transcriptome toward a unified and multimodal definition of cellular identity.","date":"2021-06-24T00:00:00Z","citationCount":1135,"authors":[{"name":"Hao Y."},{"name":"Hao S."},{"name":"Andersen-Nissen E."},{"name":"Mauck W.M."},{"name":"Zheng S."},{"name":"Butler A."},{"name":"Lee M.J."},{"name":"Wilk A.J."},{"name":"Darby C."},{"name":"Zager M."},{"name":"Hoffman P."},{"name":"Stoeckius M."},{"name":"Papalexi E."},{"name":"Mimitou E.P."},{"name":"Jain J."},{"name":"Srivastava A."},{"name":"Stuart T."},{"name":"Fleming L.M."},{"name":"Yeung B."},{"name":"Rogers A.J."},{"name":"McElrath J.M."},{"name":"Blish C.A."},{"name":"Gottardo R."},{"name":"Smibert P."},{"name":"Satija R."}],"journal":"Cell"}}],"credit":[{"name":"Andrew Butler","email":null,"url":null,"orcidid":"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3608-0463","gridid":null,"rorid":null,"fundrefid":null,"typeEntity":null,"typeRole":[],"note":null},{"name":"Saket Choudhary","email":null,"url":null,"orcidid":"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5202-7633","gridid":null,"rorid":null,"fundrefid":null,"typeEntity":null,"typeRole":[],"note":null},{"name":"Charlotte Darby","email":null,"url":null,"orcidid":"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2195-5300","gridid":null,"rorid":null,"fundrefid":null,"typeEntity":null,"typeRole":[],"note":null},{"name":"Shiwei Zheng","email":null,"url":null,"orcidid":"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6682-6743","gridid